76561198048091979,Recommended,325630,15155876,"Posted: 1 April, 2015",all,Prometheus Unbound,"Lets be brutally honest here. This game is not the most beautiful game out there. Nor is it the most well polished game mechanically speaking. Sorry devs but that is just the truth. The game has its small issues. No dodging that.But the good outweighs the bad tenfold.I really dont want to write a wall of text. So i will bullet point the good and the bad and keep each one concise:The good:A simple UI that shows you what you need to know when you need to know it. It also looks nice enough.A story mode that can be skipped. I dont know about you guys but i am not the biggest fan of story modes in a game like this. I like to just play. There is a nice sandbox mode which you can change the options for such as starting cash and so on.Random events. A lot of games do this, of course, but this feels a little more random. It wont get to a point where you realise the random events are purely scripted and tyou can predict what will happen. Wars being the best example of this. Knowing that any nation can declare war on any other nation is actually kind of fun.Freedom. Play your way. Different from story mode in that this applies to the game as a whole. You decide the best way to earn yourself money. Will you take advantage of the recent conflict that broke out? Will you decide to deal with only one part of the globe, perhaps only dealing in Asia or America? What form of transport will you use to smuggle your goods? Will you make an alliance with or destroy the competition? you get the idea.Information, information,information, in a good way. The weapons you sell all have their own factoids. And some have been updated to suit the period the game is set in. And there is a good amount about your business. Everything you need to keep the money comingRelated to my last point, info is not free when it comes to supply and demand. There are mechanics in place that require you to pay for information about a country.This game does not hold your hand. Once you have finished the tutorial you are on your own, for the most part.Small point: Agencies hunting for you. There is a most wanted list in the game. Obviously you would expect it but this game does it quite well. There is a real need to keep an eye on the different agencies in the game.Upcoming DLC that will expand the game into other criminal enterprises. Want to be the next Walter White? Well your meth labs are on their way :)The bad:The tutorial is not the best ever. Sometimes it does not provide you with enough information. And worst of all its easy to break it if you accidentally stray from the tutorial or rush ahead a little and you will find yourself with a tutorial that no longer progresses.Another small point: At this moment(without modding) you cant change things like your starting country. For me that was kind of irritating. I saw my Arms Dealer as a bit of a British gangster type.I personally dont mind the feature i am about to mention but i understand why it is silly and would not mind if it changed. Odd countries going to war. Sometimes two countries will go to war that will make no sense. Sure its a game not real life, but its an immersion breaker sometimes.I also noticed that some countries that would normally go to war with each other in a heartbeat are not available to choose when attempting to foster a war.Thats about it for the bad list. There are features i would like to see. But nothing i would consider a let down for the game. Just personal preferences.If the theme attracts you. And you like managment type games, you will like this game.I know its said a lot but just keep in mind it is an indie title. Dont judge it by AAA standards."
